               <origin>
                     <origDate calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1832" notBefore="1828">No internal date. Dated to circa 1830 by Vinson in Vinson et al. (1866-) and to 1830 by Cabaton (1912), on unstated grounds (presumably Ducler's provenance). By <persName role="scribe">Ducler's scribe</persName>, working around 1830. Probably not before 1828 (date of the earliest internally dated Ducler's manuscript). Not later than its first mention (Burnouf 1832).

</origDate>
                  <origPlace>South India, Pondicherry State, Karikal.</origPlace></origin><provenance><p>Copied for <persName xml:lang="fr" role="collector">Philippe Ducler</persName> by an unnamed copyist in Karaikal Jail. See Burnouf (1832).</p></provenance><acquisition>
                     <p>Acquired, July 22nd, 1833, from <persName xml:lang="fr" role="collector">Philippe Ducler</persName>. See BnF, département des Manuscrits, inventaire 1 = <title>Acquisitions: manuscrits et imprimés documentaires, 1833-1848</title>, no. 86.</p>
                  </acquisition></history>
